{"author":{"id":"7c5583353bae3aeeec8f21a625b5a412aebb803ab5a1165d5a45d04ef6f7f00d"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1524246445,"nonce":"HSGkzjqQLmzID21nqC/Q1iZkGKs=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM4MzE3MjEwNA==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1840#issuecomment-383172104"},"message":"@jj-umn I favor restricting the scope to querying and modifying the *data* (DML and DQL)), at least for **query_tabular** *per se*. \n\nModifying the *schema* (DDL) may make sense for **sqlite_to_tabular**, but I think not in **query_tabular**.\n\nI believe that Mark Esler looked into the possibility of having a variable number of output files and found that the Galaxy tool XML does not support it.  I am comfortable having to resort to composing a workflow if I need multiple tabular outputs.\n\nOn the other hand, it *might* be a reasonable idea, and possibly quite helpful, to compose multiple outputs into an SQLite database, so you could display multiple SQL fields only when \"Save the sqlite database in your history\" is 'Yes' -- but then you need to decide what the output tabular file should contain ... ugh.\n\nIt might be easier to understand a new **tabular_to_sqllite** tool for composing an SQLite database from tabular files, including options to set up indexes, constraints, etc..  That way you wouldn't clutter up the **query_tabular** tool with even more choices to (mis)understand.","files":null}]}